Un-rarefied Plots

first I’m going to read in the un rarefied data

metadata<-read_q2metadata("metadata_grouped.txt") # must contain q2:types in second line
SVs<-read_qza("table_grouped.qza")$data
taxonomy<-read_qza("taxonomy.qza")$data %>% parse_taxonomy()
SVs <- as.data.frame(SVs)

remove any samples (controls/blanks) that you don’t want to see in the plots

drops <- c("ctrl-1", "ctrl-2", "S-5")
SVs <- SVs[ , !(names(SVs) %in% drops)]
metadata<- metadata %>% 
  filter(`Keep`=="Yes") # to drop all banks used Keep2

for some reason after parse taxonomy d__ remain in the kingdom column, so I’ve removed it manually

taxonomy$Kingdom <- gsub("d__", "",taxonomy$Kingdom)

Species Plots

#join SVs and taxonomy with summaries at a species level
taxasums<-summarize_taxa(SVs, taxonomy)$Species

# produce heatmap with samples grouped by the type of preservative
taxa_heatmap(taxasums, metadata, "Preservative")

# produce a taxa barplot with samples grouped by preservative
taxa_barplot(taxasums, metadata, "Preservative")

Genus Plots

taxasumsgenus<-summarize_taxa(SVs, taxonomy)$Genus

taxa_heatmap(taxasumsgenus, metadata, "Preservative")

taxa_barplot(taxasumsgenus, metadata, "Preservative")

Remove Bacteria

I’m now removing Bacteria from taxasums and producing the same plots with Bacaryotes in the data

Species Plots

taxsums_noBac<- taxasums[!grepl("Bacteria.*", row.names(taxasums)),]

taxa_heatmap(taxsums_noBac, metadata, "Preservative")

taxa_barplot(taxsums_noBac, metadata, "Preservative")

Genus Plots

and without Bacteria by genus

taxsumsgenus_noBac<- taxasumsgenus[!grepl("Bacteria.*", row.names(taxasumsgenus)),]

Rarefied-126 without Bacteria

now I’m having a look at the rarefied to 126 data without bacteria

metadata<-read_q2metadata("no-blanks-metadata.txt") # must contain q2:types in second line
SVs<-read_qza("no-blanks-rarefied_table.qza")$data
taxonomy<-read_qza("taxonomy.qza")$data %>% parse_taxonomy()
SVs <- as.data.frame(SVs)
drops <- c("ctrl-1", "ctrl-2")
SVs <- SVs[ , !(names(SVs) %in% drops)]
#metadata<- metadata %>% 
#  filter(`Keep2`=="Yes")
taxonomy$Kingdom <- gsub("d__", "",taxonomy$Kingdom)

Species Plots

taxasums<-summarize_taxa(SVs, taxonomy)$Species
# removing Bacteria from taxasums
taxsums_noBac<- taxasums[!grepl("Bacteria.*", row.names(taxasums)),]

taxa_heatmap(taxsums_noBac, metadata, "Preservative")

ggsave("heatmap_rarefied126_species_noBac.pdf", height=4, width=8, device="pdf") # save a PDF 4 inches by 8 inches

taxa_barplot(taxsums_noBac, metadata, "Preservative")

ggsave("barplot_rarefied126_species_noBac.pdf", height=4, width=8, device="pdf") # save a PDF 4 inches by 8 inches

Genus Plots

taxasumsgenus<-summarize_taxa(SVs, taxonomy)$Genus

#remove Bacteria from taxasumsgenus 
taxsumsgenus_noBac<- taxasumsgenus[!grepl("Bacteria.*", row.names(taxasumsgenus)),]

taxa_heatmap(taxsumsgenus_noBac, metadata, "Preservative")

ggsave("heatmap_rarefied126_genus_noBac.pdf", height=4, width=8, device="pdf") # save a PDF 4 inches by 8 inches

taxa_barplot(taxsumsgenus_noBac, metadata, "Preservative")

ggsave("barplot_rarefied126_genus_noBac.pdf", height=4, width=8, device="pdf") # save a PDF 4 inches by 8 inches
